CREATE A NEW PROJECT:

    > composer create-project symfony/skeleton name_project

--------------------------------------------------------------
INSTALL BUNDLE with FLEX:

    > composer require name_bundle

--------------------------------------------------------------
LAUNCH SERVER

    > php -S localhost:8000 -t public/

--------------------------------------------------------------
CREATE DATABASE

    > php bin/console doctrine:database:create

--------------------------------------------------------------
SCHEMA CREATE

    > php bin/console doctrine:schema:create

--------------------------------------------------------------

CREATE ENTITY

    > php bin/console make:entity

--------------------------------------------------------------
MIGRATE ENTITY > CREATE TABLES

    > php bin/console make:migration

--------------------------------------------------------------
MIGRATE ENTITY > EXECUTE THE MIGRATIONS"'make:entity'". Message: "There are no commands defined in the "make" namespace."

    > php bin/console doctrine:migrations:migrate
--------------------------------------------------------------
UPDATE EXISTING ENTITY with CONSOLE

    > php bin/console make:entity
    > "class name ?" > NAME_ENTITY_I_WANT_UPDATE
--------------------------------------------------------------
UPDATE EXISTING ENTITY IN the code

    > php bin/console make:entity --regenerate
--------------------------------------------------------------
CREATE A CONTROLLER

    > php bin/console make:controller



JE VIENS DE CHANGER LES ENTITES POUR MANY_TO_MANY donc voir tuto zero



@Gedmo\Timestampable(on="create")
